<hl>
<seg id=1> Irish Republican Army announced an end to the fighting. </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Xinhua News agency, London, August 31st, by Wenhao Li - Today the Irish Republican Army announced that from midnight today they will cease all military activities.  Implementing a "no condition/no time limit" to the cease-fire. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The Irish Republican Army said in an announcement to the British and Irish News Media that considering the current situation and the peace progress of improving the peace in Ireland, this organization made the above decision and also informed all the other groups fighting under them. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The announcement asked the British Government to face their responsibilities and guide all the different groups to hold widespread negotiations involving all the British Government and Irish Government and all major Irish parties in order to solve the Northern Irish conflict. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> The announcement said the Irish Republican Army said that this cease fire provides an opportunity to solve the Northern Irish problem "justice fully and permanently" </seg>
<seg id=6> However, the Irish Republican Army also reminded that they will still insist "on the Republicans goal", which is to unite the whole Irish Island. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> In order to unite both Northern Ireland the Irish Republican Army, they have been fighting violently for twenty-five years. </seg>
</p>
